<div1 type="letter">

<pb facs="nei.j4c.62.29a" />

<opener>
<dateline>
121 N. Brandon Rd.<lb/>
Columbia, Mo.<lb/>
June 9, '71
</dateline>

<salute>Dear Bower:</salute>
</opener>  
<p>Where &#8212; and how &#8212; are you?! I hope this reaches you &#8212; here or in England doesn't matter &#8212; and that you will tell me if Lucile is through with her job of condensation, and if the publishing date is set. <hi rend="double underline">Please</hi>! I'm quite in the dark!</p>

<p>The Cavett show was an enormous success!! The response was the greatest ever given to any ABC network program!</p>

<p><hi rend="underline">Sacks and sacks</hi> of 

<pb facs="nei.j4c.62.29b"/>
<fw type="authorial">-2-</fw>   

letters &#8212; requests for a repetition &#8212; requests <unclear>from</unclear> many, many colleges and universities for tape copies for their <del/> archives!</p>

<p>We get requests for movie rights and <unclear>are</unclear> being a bit cagey, but soon we'll sign up for good.</p>

<p>I am still very fond <hi rend="underline">of you dear ones</hi>. For heaven's sake tell me something "awfully" nice.</p>
<closer>
<salute>With affection</salute>

<signed>John N. Gaki</signed>
</closer>

<fw type="curatorial">29</fw>

</div1>
</body>

